2. cs.COMM (Communication and Networking) - The paper is primarily concerned with communication over block-fading channels, which is a topic of interest in communication and networking research. 
3. cs.SI (Signal Processing) - The paper discusses the use of power control and multidimensional rotations/precoders at the transmitter, which are signal processing techniques. 
4. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper's focus on reliable communication over block-fading channels is relevant to networking and internet architecture research. 
5. cs.MM (Multimedia) - The paper's use of coded modulation techniques may be relevant to multimedia applications, such as video streaming.
